TY  - JOUR
TI  - The Consumption-Based Capital Asset Pricing Model
AU  - Duffie, Darrell
AU  - Zame, William
AB  - [The paper provides conditions on the primitives of a continuous-time economy under which there exist equilibria obeying the Consumption-Based Capital Asset Pricing Model (CCAPM). The paper also extends the equilibrium characterization of interest rates of Cox, Ingersoll, and Ross (1985) to multi-agent economies. We do not use a Markovian state assumption.]
